<section xml:id="sec-section-Temperature" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Temperature</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Why Temperature?
    </p>
    <sidebyside>
      <p>
      Uwera wakes up in the morning and checks the weather, it's cold and foggy with temperatures around 9°C.</p>
        <image source="/coldfog.png" width="30%">
        </image>
    </sidebyside>
    <sidebyside>
      <p>What does that mean? Will he wear a light dress or a warm jacket? </p>
        <image source="/jacket.png" width="30%">
        </image>
    </sidebyside>
    <p> Understanding temperature in math helps us make these decisions! It teaches us how to read thermometers, work with negative numbers, and even 
      convert between Degrees Celsius and kelvins. 
    </p>
   <p>Have you ever wondered why some countries use different temperature units? Or why water freezes at 0°C but boils at 100°C?
    Learning about temperature isn’t just about numbers—it helps us understand the world around us. 
    So, next time you check the weather, think about how math is helping you plan your day!
   </p>
  </introduction>  

